fix: drop expired events properly If an event has expired and no one has interested in it anymore were
end up with an exception, which is accidentally caught by
event-assigner. It treats it as slave rejection, but in reality it is
not.

This led to the evil bug, where in the case of full queue there is no
way to flush it anymore, because each expired event will present in the
queue forever (until restarted).

This commit fixes that behaviour by dropping event properly.

Thanks @antmat for helping to find this bug!

feat: add exp backoff timeout for rebalancing After any slaves death because unexpected reason
there will be rebalancing after 2 ^ N seconds where
N - number of failed attempts during specified large
time duration (32 seconds).
This allows to limit spawn rate and not to DOS an
external isolation system. Note, that these changes
are the first attempt and probably not final.

Obviously Node service already suffers from code bloat
and required refactoring and entity decomposition.

feat(node): tagged events This commit allows to wire an event with the special slave by
specifying that slaves id. It will be spawned if required and if there
are no limitations like exceeded pool limit. All events with some id
are guaranteed to be routed to slaves with the same id.

If a slave for some reasons reject the assignment the client will be
notified about it, and that event will be popped from the queue.

fix(unicorn): use indexes in callback handler instead of pointers Pointers can be reused by allocator, so a race can occur,
when a callback added to handler, released, a new other callback with
same address is added to handler and initial callback is finally called
by zookeeper.
This commit fixes this behaviour.

Correct parsing of response from Docker. Docker replies on request "/images/create" with sequence of Json objects. RapidJson can't parse such streams, because it requires stream to contain only one root object.
So before docker plugin splited response from Docker by "}{" to determine objects boundaries.
Now it parses such responses with patched RapidJson, which can read multiple objects from one stream.
This commit introduces compatibility with Docker 0.9, which sometimes puts whitespaces between some objects in response.
Fix incorrect RapidJson usage in Docker plugin. RapidJson array doesn't copy strings, which are pushed to it. Now the plugin stores all data while RapidJson object is used.

LRU cache service added. This is in memory LRU cache based on hash table and linked list with configurable maximum elements. It can be used to share values between different workers on single or different machines in effective manner. The cache supports tho methods: - put(key, value) - stores value into cache - get(key) - retrieves data from cache in form of tuple (bool, string), where bool means that this key is present in the cache, string is the value The asymptotic complexity of the cache is O(1) for both put and get.
